NAME
	video-ctl (tk-display) - build play/pause/stop/seek Tk buttons that write transport commands to a vid9p ctl file, with a label mirroring stream status

INTERFACE
	tk-display (MatrixTkDisplay + MatrixTicker)

READS
	<mount>/fmt	"<w> <h> i420 <fps>" — fps for the time readout.
	<mount>/status	state/pos/frames — mirrored into the label.

WRITES
	<mount>/ctl	"play", "pause", "stop", "seek -5000", "seek +5000"

DESCRIPTION
	The mount path is a vid9p stream directory (e.g. /mnt/video/0).
	Each button press writes one transport string to <mount>/ctl —
	exactly the wire Inferno sh or an agent uses:

	    echo pause > /mnt/video/0/ctl
	    echo 'seek +5000' > /mnt/video/0/ctl

	The playhead is vid9p SERVER state (appl/cmd/vid9p.b): these
	buttons, a video-pane's transport keys, sh, and agents all drive
	the same state, and every viewer of the stream stays in sync.
	On a live feed, stop snaps back to the live edge and seeking
	back replays the retained buffer (DVR).

	Compose beside a video-pane on the same mount; the video-player
	and video-live crystallisations in /lib/matrix/compositions are
	exactly that wiring.

SEE ALSO
